export const questionObj = {"Qtext": "
 
Consider the given figure. It is given that \(OM \parallel KJ \), and \(ON \parallel KL \). Now, prove that
\[
	\frac{IM }{IJ } = \frac{IN }{IL }
\]
\newline
tikzpicture{}
\newline

", "Steps": [{"id": "s1", "n_params": 0, "step_txt": "In triangle IJK we have $OM \parallel KJ $. So, we can write
\[
	\frac{IM }{IJ } = \frac{IO }{OK }
\]
Now, in triangle ILK , we have $ON \parallel KL $. So, we can write
\[
	\frac{IN }{IL } = \frac{IO }{IK }
\]
From the above two results, we can write that
\[
	\frac{IM }{IJ } = \frac{IN }{IL }
\]
Hence proved.
\newline

"}]}
